==English==

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛndi|-ɛndi]]

===Adjective===
'''trendy'''
# {{slang}} of, or in accordance with the latest [[trend]] or [[fashion]] [[to a fault]]
#:  ''I hate those trendy pre-wrinkled shirts.''
#:  ''The [[rims]] on that trendy [[SUV]] are really shinny.''
# {{slang}} a person obsessed with having the latest and greatest possessions [[to a fault]]
#:  ''Paris Hilton is trendy.''
# {{slang}} an activity, personal preference, or political stance that is popular due to [[hype]].
#:  ''Pretending to be a [[Lesbian]] is becoming trendy.''
#:  ''Who ever would have thought that [[Disc Golf]] would be trendy?''
# {{slang}} (''mistakenly'') of, or in accordance with the latest [[trend]] or [[fashion]], in a successful manner (esp. when used in advertising)
#:  ''All the trendiest fashions under one roof!''

